<p><strong><font color = "#C00000"Size 5>AN IMPORTANT CHANGE IN AAU POLICY RESULTING FROM AAU CONVENTION 09/25/99</strong></font></p>


<p>Important AAU Code Change:<br>

<strong>The AAU National Board of Directors amended the AAU Code as follows:</strong>

<br>302.3 Representation.  An athlete may elect to participate in his Association of bona fide residence or an Association which geographically adjoins that Association. EXCEPTION: In team sports, a maximum of three (3) athletes may participate with a team from an adjoining Association(s). Team sports include baseball, basketball (boys and girls), field hockey, flag football, hockey (ice and inline), soccer, softball, and volleyball.</p>

<p><strong>This means:</strong></br>

<p>1. An athlete must register in the Association where s/he resides.</p>

<p>2. An athlete has the choice to participate in his/her AAU Association of residence or in an AAU Association that adjoins his/her Association. Permission from the Registration Chair, Sports Chair, etc., is not required to play in an adjoining Association.</p>

<p>3. In a team sport, a maximum of 3 players from outside the Association conducting the competition may be on the roster. For example, in a Southeastern AAU event, a team could have 1 player who is a resident and registered with the Arkansas Association; 1 player who is a resident and registered with the Southern Association; and 1 player who is a resident and registered with the Georgia Association (not 3 from each Association).</p>

<p>If you have any questions relating to this rule change, please contact <A
HREF="MAILTO:jan@aausports.org">Jan Lyon, AAU Director of Association Services. </A> </p>









